Defendant Deveone Romell Peterson in court with Intern Jessica Kraft-Klehm under the supervision of attorney Rosemary Reyes Cuevas.  Benjamin Lindsay appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk: dds.

AMENDED Information filed.  Defense counsel acknowledged receipt of a copy of the Amended Information, waived its reading and entered a plea of not guilty on behalf of the defendant.  

COUNT 1 AMENDED to: CRIMINAL DAMAGE TO PROPERTY (LESS THAN $2,500 DAMAGE), contrary to Wisconsin Statutes section(s) 943.01(1), 939.51(3)(a), a Class A Misdemeanor

Defendant prepared to enter change of plea.  Hearing proceeded.  Negotiations set forth by the state.
The defendant was advised of his constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights, plead GUILTY and was examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights, Addendum to Plea Questionnaire, and Jury Instructions received and filed.  The parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis for the plea.  The Court found the defendant guilty and ordered entry of Judgment of Conviction.  

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements made by State, defense, Latreese, and defendant.  
 
The Court sentenced the defendant to serve 6 MONTHS in the House of Correction, with Huber release for employment and school, Consecutive to 14CM377 and any other sentence, with credit for 7 days served. 

The Court STAYED this sentence and placed the defendant on probation for a period of 2 YEARS with the following conditions.

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:
*Serve 30 days in the House of Correction with release privileges for employment, school, and work related HOC programs- STAYED until 8-11-14.
*Obtain AODA assessment and if necessary successfully complete follow-up treatment;
*Absolute sobriety with random urine screens and breathalyzer tests;
*No illegal drugs or association with drug community (drug users/dealers or drug houses);
*Cooperate with any and all rules set forth by the probation agent;
*No new law violations rising to the level of probable cause;
*No contact with victims Robert B. and Deonte W.;
*Obtain/maintain full time employment or full time school and part time employment;
*Obtain high school diploma or GED or HSED;
*Participate in Cognitive thinking program;
*Complete 25 hours of community service;
*Pay all supervision fees;
*Pay all applicable mandatory surcharges, costs, fees, and assessments; 

Defendant to pay all financial obligations by the end of the probation period or any remaining balance shall convert to civil judgment.  State in compliance with victim rights legislation.  The Court ordered restitution set at zero.  Defense motion for expungement granted CONTINGENT upon successful completion of EACH AND EVERY term/condition of probation.  Appeal rights given by the court. 
Filed;
- Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief;
- Pretrial Incarceration Credit;
- Sentencing Referral Form.
